    "updated_at": "2018-08-23T14:49:08Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Yep - I think since automatic getters are part of the language specification (and reflected in ABIs) they should be considered a match for the interface (which is effectively an ABI as it maps 1-1 with ABIs).\r\n\r\nThere are other oddities like my second comment above where it seems like if you're inheriting from a contract, the inheritance is done at the ABI level (so you can't redefine an existing function encoded as a public state variable) but if the public state variable is in the same contract, you're free to redefine its getter function.",
